<h2>What Are Dynamic Pricing Pages (and Why SEO Cares)</h2>
<p>Dynamic pricing pages are product or service pages where the displayed price changes based on demand, inventory, competitor data, time of day, or buyer signals. The price you see at 9 a.m. is not the price the next visitor sees at 4 p.m. Airlines, hotels, marketplaces, large ecommerce catalogs, and most SaaS pricing pages run on this model.</p>
<p>Search engine optimization cares about these pages for one blunt reason. Google indexes a snapshot. Your price changes. If the snapshot and the live page disagree, you lose trust at three layers: Merchant Center listings, rich result eligibility, and user click-through rate.</p>
<h3>Why Dynamic Pricing Pages Are Harder to Rank</h3>
<p>A static product page changes once a quarter. A dynamic pricing page can change 30 times a day. Every change is a write to your database, but only some of those writes propagate to your JSON-LD, your HTML, your title tag, and your merchant feed. The drift between layers is where rankings die.</p>
